        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-08T14:35:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not understanding how we can land this without this method using the cache. Without doing so I\u0027m not sure how it is expected to compare performance, especially on various platforms since it is known that DirectWrite and CoreText already have some cache of this information. For all we know they\u0027ve already greedily created full hash cmaps (in the case of DirectWrite this is actually fairly probable for all installed local fonts).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 272,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 272,
        "endChar": 29
